# Managed by the kensa package — do not edit by hand.
#
# Grants members of the 'kensa' group passwordless root execution of
# the systemd helper that `kensa` (agent mode) invokes for the
# service_enabled / service_disabled / service_masked handlers. The
# helper is a tightly-scoped D-Bus subprocess; sudo is its ONLY
# authorized escalation path so this file is the auditable record of
# that boundary (see specs/agent/systemd-helper.spec.yaml C-01).
#
# The 'kensa' group is created EMPTY by the package postinstall, so a
# fresh install grants this to nobody. An administrator opts a user in
# explicitly:
#
#     usermod -aG kensa <user>
#
# Canonical definition: specs/agent/systemd-helper.spec.yaml AC-09 / C-06.
%kensa ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/libexec/kensa-systemd-helper
